/*

The performance for a sequence of 2000 is 15s
```
> time ~/fuzion/clean/fuzion/build/bin/fz -e 'say (["1"," "].cycle.take 1000 .as_string "" .split " ").count'
501

real	0m6,232s
user	0m15,430s
sys	0m0,653s
```
while the performance for 4000 elements almost quadruples to 57s:
```
 > time ~/fuzion/clean/fuzion/build/bin/fz -e 'say (["1"," "].cycle.take 2000 .as_string "" .split " ").count'
1001

real	0m38,676s
user	0m57,146s
sys	0m1,348s
```
another µ-benchmark for this
```
 > time ./build/bin/fz -e 'say ((("1 1"*10000).split " " .map _->1) |> (x->sum x))'
10001

real	0m7,476s
user	0m21,208s
sys	0m0,678s
 > time ./build/bin/fz -e 'say ((("1 1"*20000).split " " .map _->1) |> (x->sum x))'
20001

real	0m23,933s
user	0m40,594s
sys	0m0,995s
```

*/

reg_issue4505 =>

  say (["1"," "].cycle.take 10000 .as_string "" .split " ").count
